Transfer student information




Students may request additional information about the Bren School undergraduate program or schedule an appointment with an academic counselor by calling the Student Affairs Office at (949) 824-5156 or contacting ucounsel@uci.edu. 
To further explore the Bren School, visit the prospective student web site.
For complete information about transfer eligibility criteria, please refer to UCI's transfer admission page. 
Inquiries about the status of your application must be directed to your counselor at the UCI Office of Admissions and Relations with Schools via the MyAdmissionsApplication message center or by calling (949) 824-6703.
The Bren School hosts several events each year in April/May  for prospective new transfer students to experience first-hand the dynamic learning environments here at UC Irvine. Applicants will be able to meet with, and hear from faculty, current students, alumni and staff.
SMART-ICS
SMART-ICS is a program that encourages partnership with area community colleges in an effort to provide student transfers to ICS subject credit for all lower division math and ICS courses required for the ICS degree.
To learn more about the program and to find out if a partnership agreement exists between the Bren School and your community college, visit the SMART-ICS page. 
 
 





